Maiharaji Altine, Gusau Zamfara State Government has lost two of its permanent secretaries following brief illnesses. The permanent secretaries are Alhaji Yawale Dango of the Office of the Head of Service and Alhaji Ahmed Sale, Ministry of Housing and Urban Development. While Sale died on Tuesday, Dango passed on last Wednesday. The deceased have been buried according to Islamic rites, The PUNCH reports. READ ALSO: China exempts more US goods from tariffs In condolence messages on behalf of Governor Matawalle, the Special Adviser on Media and Publicity, Alhaji Zailani Baffa, prayed to Allah (God) “to grant the deceased the most exalted paradise and give their families the fortitude to bear the loss”. Matawalle described the deceased as “hardworking and committed gentlemen who dedicated themselves to the services of their dear state”.